Communication Subject: IC'Alps - retour concernant le besoin d'ADC hautes performances
Communication Notes:
Bonjour Messieurs,
Nous esprons que vous avez pass de bonnes ftes et que la grippe vous a pargns ! Nous dmarrons cette nouvelle anne avec le plein dnergie et beaucoup de projets passionnants.
Nous avons mis  profit les dernires semaines pour rechercher des solutions au besoin exprim lors de notre dernier appel.
Comme voqu lors de lappel, le produit de rfrence (ADS127L11) possde des performances  ltat de lart et une figure de mrite le positionnant comme lun des meilleurs ADC dans sa catgorie. Il ne semble pas raisonnable denvisager un clone de ce circuit tout en rduisant drastiquement sa consommation.

Cependant, nous pensons quil est envisageable de concevoir un ASIC optimis en consommation (rapport 4 au moins sur le cur de lADC), en menant une rflexion suivant plusieurs axes :
-	Comprendre les performances cls en lien avec lapplication, ce qui est ngociable et ce qui ne lest pas.
-	Explorer le potentiel des nuds technologiques avancs (le circuit TI utilise un process 180 nm)
-	Envisager une intgration plus pousse : plusieurs voies par puce, fonctions complmentaires, traitement du signal etc. Tout ceci pouvant contribuer  une rduction cout/encombrement au niveau systme

Par ailleurs nous avons sollicit notre rseau et identifi des partenaires parfaitement complmentaires avec nous, et pour certains ayant contribu  des dveloppements proches du composant TI.
Nous avons dsormais une premire ide du cot dun tel dveloppement, et celui-ci serait certainement suprieur ou gal  2 M (trs dpendant du nud technologique ncessaire). Nous serions ravis den discuter avec vous en dtail  loccasion dun appel.

Quelles sont vos disponibilits dans les jours et semaines  venir ?

Cordialement

-- This email includes confidential data covered by our NDA
Christophe Gaillard  
 Senior IC Analog/MS Architect

Communication Subject: RE: Your visit on our booth at Electronica 2024

Communication Notes:
Dear Thierry,
Thank you for your project presentation. We are thrilled about the opportunity to collaborate with IC-Alps, and were eager to begin this exciting journey together. Before we proceed with the next steps, I wanted to provide a brief overview of Primosentia and the groundbreaking work were doing in the field of AI and neuromorphic computing.
About Primosentia:
Primosentia is a cutting-edge semiconductor startup focused on revolutionizing artificial intelligence through advanced neuromorphic computing technologies. As a university spinout, we are leveraging world-class research and innovative approaches to build the next generation of AI hardware capable of achieving true self-awareness and emergent behaviors. Our vision is to create machines that not only process information efficiently but also exhibit high-level cognitive functions similar to human intelligence.
The Neuromorphic Processing Unit (NPU):
At the heart of Primosentias technology is our Neuromorphic Processing Unit (NPU), designed to emulate the architecture and behavior of the human brain. Our NPU is based on biological principles of cognition, learning, and memory, and it integrates advanced features that allow machines to learn, adapt, and make decisions in real-time. The core of our NPU design includes:
	Cognitive and Emergent Behaviors: Our NPUs are engineered to process information in a way that mimics the complexity of the brain, allowing them to perform tasks that require high-level reasoning and decision-making.
	Internal Modeling and Learning: The NPU has the capability to model its environment and continuously adapt its behavior based on new experiences, creating a truly autonomous AI system.
	Neural Connectivity and Synaptic Plasticity: We are exploring innovative ways to integrate dense neural networks with sophisticated synaptic connectivity, allowing our NPUs to exhibit both long-term learning and real-time adaptability.
While the specifics of our design are proprietary, we are confident that our technology has the potential to dramatically advance the field of AI and neuromorphic computing, opening the door to new applications across industries, including robotics, autonomous systems, and cognitive AI.
Whats Next:
We are currently in the process of finalizing our first prototype and preparing it for manufacturing. We believe that with IC-Alps support, we can rapidly prototype and test this groundbreaking technology, moving closer to our vision of AI systems with true cognitive capabilities. We are excited about the opportunity to work together and explore how IC-Alps expertise can contribute to bringing our vision to life.
Please find the attached file, an award from my university which further shows strong interest in our design.
Thank you for your continued interest and for the opportunity to collaborate. Please let me know if you need any additional information. We look forward to discussing the next steps and moving forward with our partnership.
Sincerely,
Jeffrey Erhabor
Founder & CEO
Primosentia
www.primosentia.com

Objet : ASIC Design Collaboration  Neuromorphic Architecture from Academic Spinout
 
Dear ICAlps Team,
My name is Jeffrey Erhabor, and Im the founder of Primosentia, an academic spinout from the University of East London. We are developing a novel class of neuromorphic processing units (NPUs)custom ASICs that replicate brain-like learning, adaptation, and cognitive behavior directly in hardware.
Our architecture moves beyond traditional AI acceleration and introduces a biologically inspired framework for real-time learning and emergent intelligence. We are currently transitioning from schematic-level design toward fabrication and are seeking an experienced ASIC partner to help us translate, optimize, and implement this architecture for MPW or shuttle production.
Why we are reaching out to ICAlps:
         Your expertise in end-to-end ASIC development, from RTL to layout and tape-out, is exactly what we need at this pivotal stage.
         We are looking for a partner that shares our belief in breakthrough innovation, particularly in AI hardware that challenges conventional architectures.
         Collaborating with ICAlps would give us the technical strength and credibility needed to take this disruptive design to silicon and ultimately to market.
I would love to share more technical information under NDA and explore a collaboration that could define a new standard for neuromorphic systems.
Warm regards,
Jeffrey Erhabor
Founder & CEO | Primosentia
Academic Spinout, University of East London
📧 jeffreyerhabor@primosentia.com, u2488487@uel.ac.uk
🌐 www.primosentia.com

Objet : ASIC Design Collaboration  Neuromorphic Architecture from Academic Spinout
 
Dear ICAlps Team,
My name is Jeffrey Erhabor, and Im the founder of Primosentia, an academic spinout from the University of East London. We are developing a novel class of neuromorphic processing units (NPUs)custom ASICs that replicate brain-like learning, adaptation, and cognitive behavior directly in hardware.
Our architecture moves beyond traditional AI acceleration and introduces a biologically inspired framework for real-time learning and emergent intelligence. We are currently transitioning from schematic-level design toward fabrication and are seeking an experienced ASIC partner to help us translate, optimize, and implement this architecture for MPW or shuttle production.
Why we are reaching out to ICAlps:
         Your expertise in end-to-end ASIC development, from RTL to layout and tape-out, is exactly what we need at this pivotal stage.
         We are looking for a partner that shares our belief in breakthrough innovation, particularly in AI hardware that challenges conventional architectures.
         Collaborating with ICAlps would give us the technical strength and credibility needed to take this disruptive design to silicon and ultimately to market.
I would love to share more technical information under NDA and explore a collaboration that could define a new standard for neuromorphic systems.
Warm regards,
